subSubSection.paragraph:
Distribution
(
Fig. 36
). Endemic to 
Tasmania
where there are records from Poatina (
345 m
) in the central north of the island, near Ouse (
247 m
) northwest of Hobart, near around Hobart (
200–280 m
), and south to Snug (
240–264 m
). Adults have been taken from late November to late January and are sometimes locally common.

